"title": "8443: growth",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "8443",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>The process of development and maturing, used to refer to the progress of the kingdom of God and the spiritual development of believers. Scripture uses images of growth (such as seeds, plants and infants) to stress the dynamic nature of personal faith and the kingdom of God.</p>\n<h2>Images of growth</h2>\n<h3>Infancy to maturity</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:13-Eph4:15\">EPH 4:13–4:15</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:1-1Cor3:2\">1CO 3:1–3:2</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor13:11\">1CO 13:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:20\">1CO 14:20</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:12-Heb5:14\">HEB 5:12–5:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:2\">1PE 2:2</a></p>\n<h3>Seeds and plants</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke8:14-Luke8:15\">LUK 8:14–8:15</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:22-Matt13:23\">MAT 13:22–13:23</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:19-Mark4:20\">MRK 4:19–4:20</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:10\">2CO 9:10</a></p>\n<h2>The apostles worked and prayed for growth in believers</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor13:9\">2CO 13:9</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:28\">COL 1:28</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col4:12\">COL 4:12</a></p>\n<h2>Dimensions of spiritual growth</h2>\n<h3>In faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor10:15-2Cor10:16\">2CO 10:15–10:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Thess1:3\">2TH 1:3</a></p>\n<h3>In knowledge</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet3:18\">2PE 3:18</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph1:17-Eph1:18\">EPH 1:17–1:18</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph3:16-Eph3:19\">EPH 3:16–3:19</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:10\">COL 1:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:3\">2PE 1:3</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:6\">2PE 1:6</a></p>\n<h3>In love</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess4:10\">1TH 4:10</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:9\">PHP 1:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Thess3:12\">1TH 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:7-2Pet1:8\">2PE 1:7–1:8</a></p>\n<h2>Growth comes from God</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col2:19\">COL 2:19</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor3:6-1Cor3:7\">1CO 3:6–3:7</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor9:10\">2CO 9:10</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil1:6\">PHP 1:6</a></p>\n<h2>Growth comes through discipleship</h2>\n<h3>Putting away the sinful self</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Pet2:1\">1PE 2:1</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom8:13-Rom8:14\">ROM 8:13–8:14</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Cor7:1\">2CO 7:1</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal5:24\">GAL 5:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:22-Eph4:24\">EPH 4:22–4:24</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col3:5-Col3:10\">COL 3:5–3:10</a></p>\n<h3>Moving on from basic teaching</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb6:1-Heb6:2\">HEB 6:1–6:2</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Heb5:11-Heb5:14\">HEB 5:11–5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Maturing in thinking</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:20\">1CO 14:20</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Rom12:1\">ROM 12:1</a></p>\n<h3>Persevering in faith</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jas1:4\">JAS 1:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil2:12\">PHP 2:12</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Phil3:12\">PHP 3:12</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/2Pet1:5-2Pet1:8\">2PE 1:5–1:8</a></p>\n<h3>Contributing to growth in the church by exercising gifts</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:11-Eph4:12\">EPH 4:11–4:12</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor14:1-1Cor14:5\">1CO 14:1–14:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Eph4:13-Eph4:16\">EPH 4:13–4:16</a></p>\n<h2>Examples of spiritual growth in some of God's servants</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam2:26\">1SA 2:26</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke2:52\">LUK 2:52</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke1:80\">LUK 1:80</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:22\">ACT 9:22</a></p>\n<h2>The growth of the kingdom of God</h2>\n<h3>God promises that his kingdom will grow</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Col1:6\">COL 1:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt13:31-Matt13:33\">MAT 13:31–13:33</a> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:30-Mark4:32\">MRK 4:30–4:32</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke13:18-Luke13:21\">LUK 13:18–13:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark4:26-Mark4:29\">MRK 4:26–4:29</a></p>\n<h3>The early church experienced rapid numerical growth</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts4:4\">ACT 4:4</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:41\">ACT 2:41</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts2:47\">ACT 2:47</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts5:14\">ACT 5:14</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts6:7\">ACT 6:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts9:31\">ACT 9:31</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts11:21\">ACT 11:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts14:1\">ACT 14:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts16:5\">ACT 16:5</a></p>",
